  "text": "There are many other algorithms derived from PageRank that use specific tweaks to model trust or distrust in ranking schemes. [CITATION_1] considers axioms that a ranking system should satisfy and develops several ranking systems accordingly. [CITATION_2] and [CITATION_3] systematically model distrust by modifying the PageRank equations to consider negatively-weighted edges, and [CITATION_4] gives an algorithm with a similar flavor using random walks. Many of these algorithms are closely related, but rigorous analysis is desired for capturing specific phenomena. We will show that these related models can be represented by Dirichlet PageRank with appropriate boundary conditions.",
